eanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Padley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Nether Padley (Derbyshire), which is recorded as <i>Paddeley(e)</i> in the 13th century, or perhaps from Upper Padley in Hathersage or Padley Hall in Ripley (both also Derbyshire). The placenames derive from the Old English personal name <i>Pad(d)a</i> or Old English <i>padde</i> ‘toad’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert De Padley III was born in 1334, in Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Robert De Padley. He married Mrs Robert Padley. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1334–Deceased":"1334–Surnud","1334–Male":"1334–Surnud","1339–Female":"1339–Surnud","1375–Male":"1375–Surnud","1350–Male":"1350–Surnud","1334":"1334","1375":"1375","1350":"1350","1339":"1339","Hathersedge, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom":"Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1334–Deceased":"1334–Kuollut","1334–Male":"1334–Kuollut","1339–Female":"1339–Kuollut","1375–Male":"1375–Kuollut","1350–Male":"1350–Kuollut","1334":"1334","1375":"1375","1350":"1350","1339":"1339","Hathersedge, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom":"Derbyshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1334–Deceased":"1334–Décédé","1334–Male":"1334–Décédé","1339–Female":"1339–Décédée","1375–Male":"1375–Décédé","1350–Male":"1350–Décédé","1334":"1334","1375":"1375","1350":"1350","1339":"1339","Hathersedge, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom":"Derbyshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert De Padley III est né en 1334, à Derbyshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de Robert De Padley. Il a épousé Mrs Robert Padley. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1334–Deceased":"1334–Verstorben","1334–Male":"1334–Verstorben","1339–Female":"1339–Verstorben","1375–Male":"1375–Verstorben","1350–Male":"1350–Verstorben","1334":"1334","1375":"1375","1350":"1350","1339":"1339","Hathersedge, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom":"Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Robert De Padley III wurde 1334 in Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom, als Sohn von Robert De Padley geboren. Er hat Mrs Robert Padley geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1334–Deceased":"1334–Desede","